<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="014" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>C-1: Write DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md (Xrm.WebApi vs BFF)</title>
    <phase>Phase 1 — Documentation round</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>documentation, standards</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New standards document creation with explicit project constraints (DR-06). Worked examples from current code make it consumed by every future Dataverse-touching task. STANDARD per Step 3.5.5 — creates a new file with constraints, no code modification.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Publish a new standards document `docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md` defining when to
    use `Xrm.WebApi` (client-side Dataverse access from Code Pages / PCFs / web resources) versus the
    BFF (`Sprk.Bff.Api`) for Dataverse reads/writes. Include worked examples pulled directly from current
    code: at least one Xrm.WebApi case and one BFF case, with rationale tied to the decision criteria.
    Cross-link from CLAUDE.md §16. This doc binds future tasks that touch Dataverse from either side.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Technical writer with full-stack SpaarkeAi knowledge — both client-side Code Page patterns and BFF
    endpoint patterns. Bias toward concise prose with concrete from-the-repo examples; readers should be
    able to scan the doc and reach a placement decision in &lt;3 minutes.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md` exists with: (1) decision criteria (when to use
    Xrm.WebApi vs BFF — auth, complexity, cross-system, audit, AI involvement, etc.); (2) at least one
    worked example for each direction pulled from current code; (3) anti-patterns (e.g., "do not call
    Xrm.WebApi from server-side code", "do not double-write via both paths"); (4) cross-link from CLAUDE.md
    §16; (5) explicit reference to CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene for the BFF-side decision.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec DR-06 + plan §4 Phase 1 C-1: SpaarkeAi makes Dataverse reads/writes from both client
      (Xrm.WebApi from Code Pages / PCFs) and server (BFF from .NET). Without explicit criteria, new code
      tends to default to whichever pattern the author saw last, leading to drift and operational
      surprises. CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene already governs the BFF side; this doc adds the client-side
      decision frame and reconciles the two.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/CODING-STANDARDS.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/INTEGRATION-CONTRACTS.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Doc MUST cover both directions: when to use Xrm.WebApi (client) and when to use BFF (server-mediated). Don't favor one over the other in the framing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Doc MUST include at least one worked example for each direction, pulled from current shipped code (e.g., a Code Page using Xrm.WebApi for a quick section read; a BFF endpoint mediating an AI-involved write).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Decision criteria MUST address: auth model (Xrm session vs BFF auth v2), data complexity (single record vs cross-system), AI involvement (BFF if AI is in the path), audit trail requirements, error handling, retry semantics, rate limits.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Doc MUST cross-link to CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene + `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` — the BFF-side decision criteria already live there; this doc references rather than duplicates.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Doc MUST be cross-linked from CLAUDE.md §16 — add the link in this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Reference ADR-028 in the auth-model criterion. Client-side via `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`; no token snapshots.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/plan.original.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/CODING-STANDARDS.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/INTEGRATION-CONTRACTS.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/ANTI-PATTERNS.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read prior art">Read existing standards docs and `bff-extensions.md`. Identify where the BFF-side criteria already live; the new doc references rather than duplicates.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Survey real code">Find 2-3 examples of each pattern in current code (Xrm.WebApi from a Code Page / PCF; BFF endpoint mediating Dataverse). Pick the cleanest one of each to use as the worked example.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Draft criteria">Write the decision criteria section: auth model, data complexity, AI involvement, audit, error handling, retries, rate limits. Each criterion is one paragraph.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Draft worked examples">Write the Xrm.WebApi example (with code snippet + rationale tied to criteria) and the BFF example.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Draft anti-patterns + cross-links">Add anti-patterns ("don't call Xrm.WebApi from server", "don't double-write via both"). Add cross-link to CLAUDE.md §10 + bff-extensions.md. Update CLAUDE.md §16 to point to this doc.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify">Walk through 3 hypothetical Dataverse access scenarios and confirm the criteria reach the right choice each time.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Change task 014 status to ✅ completed in `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document deviations">If any deviation from spec DR-06 or plan §4, write to `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read prior standards docs + bff-extensions</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Find Xrm.WebApi and BFF Dataverse access patterns in code</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create the new standards doc</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Update CLAUDE.md §16 pointer</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md (new)</output>
    <output type="docs">CLAUDE.md (§16 pointer added)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md` exists with decision criteria covering all 7 dimensions: auth, complexity, AI, audit, error handling, retries, rate limits.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Doc includes ≥1 worked example each from current code: one Xrm.WebApi, one BFF.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Doc cross-links to CLAUDE.md §10 + `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` — does not duplicate the BFF-side criteria.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">CLAUDE.md §16 pointer added to the new doc.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">3-scenario walk-through in verify step reaches the correct placement each time.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    This task MUST be executed via the `task-execute` skill from `.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md`.
    STANDARD rigor — new standards document. Quality gates SKIPPED per Step 0.5.
